{
  "texts": [
    "According to (Yang et al. 2022), the traditional Blockchain architecture is composed of several layers, including the data layer, network layer, consensus layer, incentive layer, contract layer, and application layer.",
    "The relationship between these layers and the Metaverse is described as follows:",
    "The mechanisms for transmitting and verifying data provide network support for various forms of data transfer and verification of the economic system in the Metaverse. 2.",
    "The credit problem of Metaverse transactions can be addressed through consensus mechanisms. 3.",
    "Blockchain-distributed storage guarantees the safety of digital assets and the identities of Metaverse users. 4."
  ]
}